Google-Directions

Interface to the Directions API V3 from Google to get driving, walking or cycling directions

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Google::Directions

You can also look for information at:

    Github for latest versions, or pushing change requests
	https://github.com/robin13/Google-Directions

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Google-Directions

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Google-Directions

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Google-Directions

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Google-Directions/


